{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, most existing research has focused on English-language models, overlooking the global diversity of language use and the different cultural dimensions of bias [7], [12], [17]- [21].",
    "This has left a significant gap in our understanding of LLM fairness and bias, underscoring the need for more comprehensive and inclusive research approaches.This article aims to bridge these gaps by conducting a comparative analysis of bias and fairness across multiple LLMs, including ChatGPT-4, Google Gemini, and Llama 2, utilizing the Google BIG-Bench benchmark [22].",
    "By evaluating the effectiveness of different benchmarks in detecting and mitigating biases, this study seeks to identify which frameworks are most effective at ensuring fairness in LLMs.",
    "The scope of this research extends beyond the technical evaluation of model biases, exploring the implications of these biases on societal norms and values.",
    "Through this comparative analysis, the article contributes to the broader discourse on AI ethics, offering insights into the development of more equitable and responsible AI technologies.This study makes several significant contributions to the field of AI fairness and bias in Large Language Models (LLMs):1) It provides a comprehensive comparative analysis of bias and fairness across three state-of-the-art LLMs: ChatGPT-4, Google Gemini, and Llama 2, utilizing the Google BIG-Bench benchmark.2) The study introduces a detailed evaluation framework that combines both quantitative and qualitative measures to assess model bias and fairness, offering insights into the sophisticated nature of AI ethics.3) It highlights the strengths and limitations of the Google BIG-Bench as a benchmarking tool for assessing fairness and bias in LLMs, contributing to the ongoing discussion on effective benchmarking practices in AI research."
  ]
}